# Permissions Rules

- Deny by default; require explicit authentication/authorization.
- Protect mutating operations with policies/permissions checks.
- Enforce least privilege for admin actions.
- Do not expose tenant-sensitive fields in unauthorized responses.
- Prefer centralized policy checks over duplicated inline role checks.
- Ensure permission changes are logged with actor + target context.
